We start with the following simple observation:

\begin{lemma}\label{lem-rank}
Assume $(f,A)$ is an analytic cocycle over a compact, connected  measure space $({\mathbb X},\mu)$. 
There is $r$ such that for all $x$ except a union of sub-manifolds of zero measure (w.r.t. $\mu$), ${\operatorname{{\rm rank}}} (A(x))=r$ and ${\operatorname{{\rm rank}}}(A(x))\leq r$ for all $x$.
\end{lemma}
\begin{proof} 
Let $r=\max_{x} {\operatorname{{\rm rank}}} A(x)$, such that ${\operatorname{{\rm rank}}} A(x)\leq r$ for all $x$. Then, $\Lambda^r A(x) \neq {\bf 0}$ for some $x$ and the equation ${\operatorname{{\rm rank}}} A(x)<r$ is equivalent to $\Lambda^r A(x)={\bf 0}$. 
